The court dismissed the appeal of the outgoing Emir of Kano - Muhammad Adamu - Freedom Radio Nigeria.
Nigeria's Chief Superintendent of Police, Muhammad Adamu, has urged the High Court in Abuja to dismiss the appeal filed by the outgoing Emir of Kano, Muhammdu Sunusi, preventing him from entering Kano State.
According to Adamu, the court did not have jurisdiction to hear the case brought before it by the abdicating King.
This was disclosed by the Inspector General of Police, who spoke to reporters in Abuja.
According to him, the court suspended the case without delay, for some time.
Since 9 March this year, the Kano State government has removed Muhammad Sunusi from power.
Nigeria has changed the date of return of flights to foreign countries.
Publish date: 27/08/2020 - 20:38
The Nigerian government has announced the suspension of international air travel scheduled to begin on 29 June due to an increase in coronavirus cases.
The country's aviation ministry said President Muhammadu Buhari had ordered the suspension of air traffic control so as not to open the door for international carriers to spread the virus further.
According to the statement, the opening of the country's gates will be delayed until September 5.
Nigeria had its first case of coronavirus in February when an Italian national entered the country.
So far, more than 50,000 people have been infected in Nigeria and more than 1,000 have died.
